    </div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The <strong>CodeSearchIndex Result Class</strong> (Comserv::Model::Schema::Ency::Result::CodeSearchIndex) is a DBIx::Class Result class that manages a searchable index of code files with extracted code elements and role-based access control. It stores file paths, file types, searchable code content, extracted code elements (functions, classes, variables), and controls access based on user roles.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This class enables efficient code searching and discovery with proper access restrictions, maintaining a content hash for change detection and automatic indexing timestamps. It supports multiple file types (Perl modules, Template Toolkit, SQL) and provides helper methods for accessing and filtering code elements.</p>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <strong>Initial Release (v0.01 - 2026-01-11)</strong>: Complete documentation of CodeSearchIndex Result class including schema definition, field descriptions, helper methods, and code element extraction patterns.
            </div>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PREREQUISITES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="prerequisites" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Perl 5.20 or later</li>
                <li>DBIx::Class ORM (v0.08194 or later)</li>
                <li>Comserv application instance with ENCY database</li>
                <li>JSON support for code_elements storage</li>
                <li>MariaDB/MySQL with codesearchindex table</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- KEY FEATURES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="features" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Key Features</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Multi-File Type Support</strong>: Index Perl modules (.pm), Template Toolkit (.tt), and SQL files</li>
                <li><strong>Code Element Extraction</strong>: Extract and store functions, classes, and variables in JSON format</li>
                <li><strong>Searchable Content</strong>: Store full searchable code content with longtext field</li>
                <li><strong>Change Detection</strong>: Content hash tracks file modifications for incremental indexing</li>
                <li><strong>Role-Based Access</strong>: Control visibility based on user roles (developer, admin)</li>
                <li><strong>Unique File Paths</strong>: Prevent duplicate entries for the same code file</li>
                <li><strong>File Metadata</strong>: Track file size and automatic indexing timestamps</li>
                <li><strong>Helper Methods</strong>: Convenient accessors for code elements, functions, classes, and variables</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SCHEMA SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="schema" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Schema Definition</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.1 Table: codesearchindex</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Primary table: <code>codesearchindex</code></p>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.2 Column Definitions</h3>
            <table border="1" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <th style="padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Column</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Type</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Nullable</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Default</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>id</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">INTEGER</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Auto-increment</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Primary key - unique index entry identifier</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>file_path</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">VARCHAR(512)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Full path to the indexed code file (unique)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>file_type</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">ENUM('pm', 'tt', 'sql')</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Type of file being indexed (pm=Perl, tt=Template Toolkit, sql=SQL)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>code_elements</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">JSON</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">YES</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NULL</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Extracted code elements (functions, classes, variables) in JSON format</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>searchable_code</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">LONGTEXT</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Full searchable code content for full-text search</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>content_hash</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">VARCHAR(64)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">SHA-256 hash of file content for change detection</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>indexed_at</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">TIMESTAMP</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">When the file was indexed</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>min_role</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">ENUM('developer', 'admin')</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NO</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Minimum role required to access this indexed code (developer=visible to all, admin=admins only)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>file_size</code></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">INTEGER</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">YES</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">NULL</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Size of the file in bytes for indexing statistics</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- METHODS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="methods" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Result Class Methods</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.1 get_code_elements</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Retrieve all extracted code elements as a hash.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Signature:</strong></p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">$elements = $index->get_code_elements();
</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Hash reference containing code elements, or empty hash if none exist.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.2 get_functions</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Extract list of functions defined in the indexed code.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Signature:</strong></p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">$functions = $index->get_functions();
</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Array reference of function names/definitions, or empty array if none.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.3 get_classes</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Extract list of classes defined in the indexed code.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Signature:</strong></p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">$classes = $index->get_classes();
</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Array reference of class names/definitions, or empty array if none.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.4 get_variables</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Extract list of variables defined in the indexed code.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Signature:</strong></p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">$variables = $index->get_variables();
</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Array reference of variable names/definitions, or empty array if none.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.5 is_accessible_by_role</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Check if a user with a specific role can access this indexed code.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Signature:</strong></p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">$accessible = $index->is_accessible_by_role($user_role);
</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>$user_role: User's role string ('developer', 'admin', etc.)</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Boolean (1 if accessible, 0 if not). Admins always have access.</p>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- USAGE EXAMPLES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="usage-examples" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Usage Examples</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.1 Search Code Index by File Path</h3>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">use Comserv::Model::Schema::Ency::Result::CodeSearchIndex;

my $schema = $c->model('DBEncy')->schema;

# Find index entry for a specific file
my $index = $schema->resultset('CodeSearchIndex')->search({
    file_path => 'lib/Comserv/Controller/Admin.pm'
})->first;

if ($index) {
    print "File indexed at: " . $index->indexed_at . "\n";
    print "File size: " . $index->file_size . " bytes\n";
}
</pre>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.2 Search for Specific Function</h3>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">my $schema = $c->model('DBEncy')->schema;

# Search for files containing a specific function
my @results = $schema->resultset('CodeSearchIndex')->search({
    searchable_code => { -like => '%sub my_function%' }
}, { rows => 10 })->all;

foreach my $result (@results) {
    print "Found in: " . $result->file_path . "\n";
}
</pre>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.3 Get Code Elements for a File</h3>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">my $index = $schema->resultset('CodeSearchIndex')->find($id);

# Get all extracted code elements
my $elements = $index->get_code_elements();

# Get specific element types
my $functions = $index->get_functions();
my $classes = $index->get_classes();
my $variables = $index->get_variables();

print "Functions: " . join(", ", @$functions) . "\n";
print "Classes: " . join(", ", @$classes) . "\n";
</pre>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.4 Check Access by User Role</h3>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">my $index = $schema->resultset('CodeSearchIndex')->find($id);
my $user_role = $c->user->get('role');

if ($index->is_accessible_by_role($user_role)) {
    # Display the indexed code to user
    print $index->searchable_code;
} else {
    print "You do not have permission to view this code.\n";
}
</pre>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.5 Find All Recently Indexed Files</h3>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">my $schema = $c->model('DBEncy')->schema;

# Find files indexed in the last hour
my $one_hour_ago = DateTime->now->subtract(hours => 1)->iso8601;

my @recent = $schema->resultset('CodeSearchIndex')->search({
    indexed_at => { '>' => $one_hour_ago }
}, { order_by => 'indexed_at DESC' })->all;

foreach my $index (@recent) {
    print "File: " . $index->file_path . "\n";
    print "Indexed: " . $index->indexed_at . "\n";
}
</pre>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CODE ELEMENTS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="code-elements" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Code Elements Structure</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7.1 JSON Structure</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The <code>code_elements</code> field stores extracted code elements in JSON format with the following structure:</p>
            <pre style="background-color: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;">{
    "functions": [
        "function_name_1",
        "function_name_2"
    ],
    "classes": [
        "ClassName1",
        "ClassName2"
    ],
    "variables": [
        "$var_name_1",
        "$var_name_2"
    ]
}
</pre>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7.2 File Types and Supported Elements</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>pm (Perl Module)</strong>: Extracts subroutines, packages, and variables</li>
                <li><strong>tt (Template Toolkit)</strong>: Extracts blocks, filters, and template functions</li>
                <li><strong>sql (SQL Files)</strong>: Extracts table names, procedures, and functions</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

